{{Quote|But how do you know I won't slip in an actual creature to fight against you? You would never know the difference, the holo-remotes are so realistic. And if you stand there and refuse to fight, a real enemy might just remove your head from your shoulders.|[[Brakiss]], to [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]]|<ref name="Young Jedi Knights: Shadow Academy">''[[Young Jedi Knights: Shadow Academy]]''</ref>}}
'''Holo-remotes''' were extremely sophisticated and realistically rendered [[Hologram/Legends|holograms]] used for self-defense training. To create a functioning holo-remote, a grid of computer sensors was set up within a room so that the computer controlling the [[Holoprojector/Legends|holoprojector]] could track the movements of the user and simulate realistic hit detection on the part of the hologram that was being projected. Though the result would be a realistic depiction of an adversary, the hologram itself could do no harm to the user.

